          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650987969770-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650987969770-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650987969770-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tilapia is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>courgette </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until all the veg has fully softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1650987973585-x200.jpg",
